body:
### Component

Forge

### Describe the feature you would like

Currently, Foundry test can access most traces of call execution, via `startStateDiffRecording()`, 
which eventually returns an array `AccountAccess[]`, with account references and storage access.
However, the one thing that is not returned is the actual executed bytecodes.

This is something that we do need for [erc4337](https://ercs.ethereum.org/ERCS/erc-4337) implementation
(in short: smart wallet contracts must perform validation while avoiding some code patterns. We have enough information for validation storage access, but we also need to verify opcode usage.

### Suggestion.
Instead of overloading the returned struct of `stopAndReturnStateDiff()`, we can add a new method 
```
function getStateDiffOpcodes(uint index) returns (OpcodeAccess[] memory)
```
The "index" parameter is the same index into the array returned by: `stopAndReturnStateDiff()`
That is, for each `AccountAccess` entry, we return a array of opcodes

```
struct OpcodeAccess {
  uint8 opcode;
  uint pc;
  uint gasCost;
  uint gas;
  uint depth;
}
```

